                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, rather careless</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid crimson).</seg>
                        <date>First half of the 19th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor and his family
                           members (the whole name or the second component); 1st, 2nd, 5th 6th, 17th
                           and 18th line on the incipit page; two initial lines of the sub-sections;
                           names of the months on fols. 76r, 81rb; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of the chapter dividers (e.g., fol. 32va); elements of
                           Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The quality of the handwriting
                        deteriorates esp. on <locus from="33v" to="34r">33v-34r</locus>,
                        79r.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#95va">f. 95va</locus>
                           <desc>-b: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in the main hand. It contains the names of the
                              donor Walda Māryām, as well as his father Gabra Wahǝd, his mother
                              Walatta ʾAnanya and the older variant of the church name, i.e., Qärnä
                              Säbär. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The names of the donors and nomina sacra are sometimes
                           written in the supplication formulas, in a secondary hand: <locus target="#17vb">17vb</locus>, 22rab, 28ra, 31ra, 32ra, 78rb).
 -
                           Writing exercises and doodles: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 11v, 12r,
                           25v, 39v, 46v, 47r, 61r, 84r, 96rv.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Monthly readings are indicated by the names of the
                              months written, with decoration, in the upper margin of fols: 3r,
                              11vb, 18va, 32ra (in pen), 57rb, 61vb, 81rb, 85rb, 90r.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
